name: 02-Data Exploration and Data Segmentation Modelling
content:
Data Description and Preparation

Data Description (from dataset):

The dataset contains customer demographics, service usage, call patterns, financial metrics, and churn details. Key attributes include:

  • Demographic Features:
  • AgeHH1, AgeHH2, ChildrenInHH, ServiceArea.
  • Revenue & Usage Features:
  • MonthlyRevenue, MonthlyMinutes, OverageMinutes, RoamingCalls.
  • Churn/Retention Features:
  • Churn, RetentionCalls, RetentionOffersAccepted.
  • Call Quality Metrics:
  • DroppedCalls, BlockedCalls, UnansweredCalls, CustomerCareCalls.
  • Equipment & Subscription Features:
  • Handsets, HandsetModels, CurrentEquipmentDays, UniqueSubs.

Target Variable:

  • While clustering is unsupervised, churn (Churn: Yes/No) is used as a profiling attribute to understand segment-level risks.

Data Preparation Steps:

  1. Data Cleaning:
  • Handle missing values in revenue, minutes, and equipment attributes.
  • Treat outliers in usage-related metrics (OverageMinutes, RoamingCalls).
  1. Feature Engineering:
  • Calculate % change metrics: PercChangeMinutes, PercChangeRevenues.
  • Generate normalized usage ratios (e.g., calls per subscription, revenue per minute).
  1. Encoding & Transformation:
  • Encode categorical variables (ServiceArea, churn).
  • Standardize numerical variables to ensure K-means clustering accuracy.
  1. Clustering Preparation:
  • Select optimal set of variables for clustering (revenue, usage, churn indicators, retention).
